
---


@startuml

' Define package
package "E-Home-2020 System" {

    ' Core Entities
    class Sensor {
        +String vendorId
        +String description
        +String unit
        +Room room
        +List<Measurement> measurements
        +float getLastValue()
        +void addMeasurement(Measurement m)
    }

    class TemperatureSensor extends Sensor {
        +float min
        +float max
    }

    class PowerSensor extends Sensor {
        +float totalConsumption
    }

    class Measurement {
        +Timestamp timestamp
        +float value
    }

    class Room {
        +String description
        +List<Sensor> sensors
    }

    class Apartment {
        +String address
        +List<Room> rooms
        +List<Inhabitant> inhabitants
        +String email
    }

    class Inhabitant {
        +String username
        +String password
        +Boolean isAdmin
        +Apartment apartment
        +void querySensorData(Sensor s)
        +void setThreshold(Sensor s, float threshold)
    }

    class SensorController {
        +List<Apartment> apartments
        +List<Sensor> sensors
        +void authenticateUser(String username, String password)
        +void storeApartment(Apartment a)
        +void assignSensorToRoom(Sensor s, Room r)
    }

    class EMonitor {
        +void checkThresholds()
        +void sendAlertEmail(String email, String message)
    }

}

' Relationships

Apartment "1" -- "many" Room : contains
Room "1" -- "many" Sensor : contains
Apartment "1" -- "many" Inhabitant : has
SensorController "1" -- "many" Apartment : manages
SensorController "1" -- "many" Sensor : manages
Inhabitant "1" -- "1" Apartment : belongs to
EMonitor ..> SensorController : uses
EMonitor ..> Inhabitant : sends alerts to

@enduml

---

### 📌 Notes on the Diagram:

- **Inheritance**: `TemperatureSensor` and `PowerSensor` inherit from the base class `Sensor`.
- **Aggregation/Composition**:
  - An `Apartment` contains multiple `Room`s.
  - A `Room` contains multiple `Sensor`s.
  - A `Sensor` has multiple `Measurement`s.
- **Associations**:
  - The `SensorController` manages `Sensors` and `Apartments`.
  - `Inhabitants` belong to an `Apartment`.
  - `EMonitor` interacts with the `SensorController` to monitor thresholds and send alerts.
- **Dependencies**:
  - `EMonitor` depends on `Inhabitant` to send alert emails if an email is available.

